<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Willamette River (Salem / Keizer stretch)</strong><br>
        This stretch is a hotspot for both smallmouth and largemouth bass. Anglers report consistent catches around bridge pilings and deep-water structures 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Minto‑Brown Island Park (Willamette sloughs &amp; ponds)</strong><br>
        A local favorite with several sloughs and ponds teeming with bass. Bank access is available, and float tubes are ideal for getting into the deeper channels 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Keizer Rapids Park &amp; Wheatland Ferry area</strong><br>
        Offers boat ramps and sloughs known for their “monster” bass potential 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Walter Wirth Lake</strong><br>
        Easily accessible, within Cascade Gateway Park. Stocked with trout but also home to largemouth bass and panfish—ideal for bank anglers&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Other Notable Fishing Locations
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Walling Pond &amp; St. Louis Ponds</strong><br>
        Known more for stocked trout and panfish, though warmwater fish are present 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Santiam River &amp; North Fork reservoirs (e.g., Detroit Lake)</strong><br>
        A short drive east yields both trout and smallmouth bass in scenic reservoir settings&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
